<abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Handwritten copies in one of the bound volumes used by the team of clerks on GW's headquarters staff who worked from 1781-83 under the direction of Lt. Col. Richard Varick to record correspondence, orders, instructions, and related items from GWs Revolutionary War papers ]">Varick transcript</abbr>, <span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ U.S. Library of Congress, George Washington Papers, Washington, D.C. ]">DLC:GW</span>.
</p>

</div>
<div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-02-02-0557-fn-0001-ptr" id="GEWN-03-02-02-0557-fn-0001">1</a>

   <p>For Schuylers response, see <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-03-03-02-0021" class="document">Schuyler to GW, 57 Jan. 1776</a>.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-02-02-0557-fn-0002-ptr" id="GEWN-03-02-02-0557-fn-0002">2</a>
	
   <p>GW enclosed the letters captured with the sloop <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Betsey</span> in his <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-03-02-02-0528" class="document">letter to Hancock of 18 December</a>.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-02-02-0557-fn-0003-ptr" id="GEWN-03-02-02-0557-fn-0003">3</a>

   <p>See <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-03-02-02-0529" class="document">GW to Howe, 18 Dec.</a>, and <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-03-02-02-0543" class="document">Howe to GW, 21 Dec. 1775</a>.</p>

</div>
